Cashbuild, Datacentrix and Remgro Could Move: South African Stocks Preview

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-06-20T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/cashbuild-datacentrix-remgro-south-africa-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index declined 41.61 or 0.1
percent, to 30,627.65 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Cashbuild Ltd. (CSB)  : The building materials retailer
said it is finalizing a black economic empowerment transaction
aimed at incentivizing top performing managers. The shares
dropped 1.50 rand, or 1.6 percent, to 94.50 rand.  Datacentrix Holdings Ltd. (DCT)  : The computer-services
company declared a dividend of 9.18 cents per share for the year
ended Feb. 28. Its shares dropped 4 cents, or 0.9 percent, to
4.35 rand.  Remgro Ltd. (REM)  : The investment holding company with
interests in banks, mining, and wine and spirits releases
results for the year though March. The shares rose 1.05 rand, or
1 percent, to 109.20 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Brand in Cape Town Nef at 
